		title		: "Lesson 8: Are You Busy?",
		text		: "1\n00:00:19,914 --> 00:00:21,927\nHello, everyone.\n\n2\n00:00:22,027 --> 00:00:23,939\nHere I am at my new job!\n\n3\n00:00:24,139 --> 00:00:27,362\nYesterday at my first day of work …\n\n4\n00:00:38,490 --> 00:00:40,301\nlet’s not talk about yesterday.\n\n5\n00:00:40,404 --> 00:00:42,317\nToday is a new day!\n\n6\n00:00:42,524 --> 00:00:46,254\nToday I want to apologize to my co-workers.\n\n7\n00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:51,748\nHi, Anne. Are you busy?\n\n8\n00:00:52,056 --> 00:00:52,857\nHi, Anna.\n\n9\n00:00:53,068 --> 00:00:55,075\nYes. At 10 a.m.\n\n10\n00:00:55,276 --> 00:00:56,784\nI am writing.\n\n11\n00:00:57,086 --> 00:00:59,808\nEvery day I do my morning show.\n\n12\n00:01:00,111 --> 00:01:01,520\nSorry!\n\n13\n00:01:01,822 --> 00:01:05,847\nOkay. See you later, maybe.\n\n14\n00:01:06,350 --> 00:01:08,464\nMaybe I’ll see you later.\n\n15\n00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:25,577\nHi, Jonathan. Are you busy?\n\n16\n00:01:25,681 --> 00:01:27,191\nYes, I’m busy.\n\n17\n00:01:27,412 --> 00:01:31,841\nWhen the studio light is on, I am recording my evening show.\n\n18\n00:01:32,046 --> 00:01:33,173\nRight.\n\n19\n00:01:33,173 --> 00:01:34,387\nSorry about yesterday.\n\n20\n00:01:34,496 --> 00:01:35,704\nNo worries.\n\n21\n00:01:35,815 --> 00:01:37,023\nMay I see the studio?\n\n22\n00:01:37,124 --> 00:01:38,331\nUm, maybe another time?\n\n23\n00:01:38,546 --> 00:01:40,359\nRight now I am busy.\n\n24\n00:01:40,568 --> 00:01:43,687\nSure. Okay, ’bye.\n\n25\n00:01:43,788 --> 00:01:44,894\n‘Bye.\n\n26\n00:02:17,037 --> 00:02:19,448\nHi, Amelia! Are you busy?\n\n27\n00:02:19,653 --> 00:02:20,962\nI’m a little busy.\n\n28\n00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:25,290\nI want to say I’m sorry for yesterday.\n\n29\n00:02:25,602 --> 00:02:26,911\nIt’s okay, Anna.\n\n30\n00:02:27,122 --> 00:02:28,552\nWell, I am sorry.\n\n31\n00:02:28,653 --> 00:02:29,960\nIt’s okay, Anna.\n\n32\n00:02:30,068 --> 00:02:31,378\nCome by this afternoon.\n\n33\n00:02:31,501 --> 00:02:32,609\nOkay.\n\n34\n00:03:01,199 --> 00:03:02,509\nAnna.\n\n35\n00:03:03,114 --> 00:03:04,523\nYes, Ms. Weaver.\n\n36\n00:03:04,624 --> 00:03:05,629\nAre you busy?\n\n37\n00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:06,641\nYes, Ms. Weaver.\n\n38\n00:03:06,775 --> 00:03:07,680\nI am busy.\n\n39\n00:03:07,797 --> 00:03:10,023\nMy office. 5:00 p.m.\n\n40\n00:03:10,738 --> 00:03:13,155\n5:00 p.m.\n\n41\n00:03:27,152 --> 00:03:28,561\nCome in.\n\n42\n00:03:31,799 --> 00:03:34,520\nSurprise!\n\n43\n00:03:34,749 --> 00:03:36,259\nA party!\n\n44\n00:03:36,591 --> 00:03:37,497\nAwesome!\n\n45\n00:03:38,420 --> 00:03:41,542\nAnd I still have my job! Phew!*\n\n46\n00:03:41,952 --> 00:03:43,061\nUntil next time!\n\n47\n00:03:43,820 --> 00:03:49,364\n* Phew! is a sound used to show that you are relieved, tired, or hot",
