		title		: "Lesson 11: This Is My Neighborhood",
		text		: "1\n00:00:16,959 --> 00:00:21,500\nHello! DC is a city for walking.\n\n2\n00:00:21,601 --> 00:00:25,217\nIn our neighborhood, I can do all my errands.\n\n3\n00:00:25,419 --> 00:00:28,031\nMarsha, before we get ice cream,\n\n4\n00:00:28,132 --> 00:00:31,449\nI need to return three books to the library.\n\n5\n00:00:31,656 --> 00:00:33,570\nWhere is the library?\n\n6\n00:00:33,670 --> 00:00:37,293\nIt is on this street on the corner.\n\n7\n00:00:37,594 --> 00:00:38,600\nAwesome!\n\n8\n00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:39,712\nLet's go!\n\n9\n00:00:53,549 --> 00:00:56,064\nMarsha, I can return the books here.\n\n10\n00:00:56,266 --> 00:01:02,400\nAnna, what are those in the books?\n\n11\n00:01:02,601 --> 00:01:10,656\nMarsha, these are letters to my family and friends back home … four letters!\n\n12\n00:01:10,863 --> 00:01:12,683\nIs there a post office near here?\n\n13\n00:01:12,888 --> 00:01:14,901\nUm, no.\n\n14\n00:01:15,102 --> 00:01:17,417\nThe post office is far from here.\n\n15\n00:01:17,519 --> 00:01:20,442\nBut there is a mailbox across from the store.\n\n16\n00:01:20,542 --> 00:01:21,951\nAwesome! Let’s go!\n\n17\n00:01:29,626 --> 00:01:31,741\nMarsha, now I need to buy stamps.\n\n18\n00:01:31,841 --> 00:01:33,558\nDo you have cash?\n\n19\n00:01:33,768 --> 00:01:35,986\nNo. Is there a bank near here?\n\n20\n00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:38,002\nThere is a bank behind you.\n\n21\n00:01:38,103 --> 00:01:40,116\nThanks, Marsha.\n\n22\n00:01:40,221 --> 00:01:42,033\nYou know our neighborhood so well.\n\n23\n00:02:05,385 --> 00:02:06,894\nNow I have cash.\n\n24\n00:02:07,005 --> 00:02:08,514\nI can buy stamps.\n\n25\n00:02:08,917 --> 00:02:11,333\nThat store sells stamps.\n\n26\n00:02:11,547 --> 00:02:12,552\nWait here.\n\n27\n00:02:14,492 --> 00:02:15,805\nI have stamps.\n\n28\n00:02:15,913 --> 00:02:17,223\nWow, you’re fast.\n\n29\n00:02:18,091 --> 00:02:25,838\nThank you, thank you letters, for sending my words… my love … to my family and friends -\n\n30\n00:02:29,815 --> 00:02:33,037\nDo you have more cash?\n\n31\n00:02:33,138 --> 00:02:34,546\nI do!\n\n32\n00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:37,374\nIce cream!!\n\n33\n00:02:39,936 --> 00:02:41,950\nI love my new neighborhood!\n\n34\n00:02:42,252 --> 00:02:44,364\nEverything is near our apartment!\n\n35\n00:02:44,675 --> 00:02:48,804\nEven hair salons*, and ice cream!\n\n36\n00:02:49,005 --> 00:02:50,213\nUntil next time!\n\n37\n00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:56,665\n*salon - n. a business that gives customers beauty treatments (such as haircuts)\n\n38\n00:02:54,065 --> 00:02:57,694\nHello! DC is a city for walking.\n\n39\n00:02:57,794 --> 00:03:02,028\nIn our neighborhood, I can do all my errands.\n\n40\n00:03:02,137 --> 00:03:05,262\nMarsha, before we get ice cream,\n\n41\n00:03:05,364 --> 00:03:08,589\nI need to return three books to the library.\n\n42\n00:03:09,219 --> 00:03:10,825\nWhere is the library?\n\n43\n00:03:11,028 --> 00:03:13,747\nIt is on this street on the corner.\n\n44\n00:03:13,949 --> 00:03:15,259\nAwesome!\n\n45\n00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:16,466\nLet's go!\n\n46\n00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:21,308\nMarsha, I can return the books here.\n\n47\n00:03:22,701 --> 00:03:27,231\nAnna, what are those in the books?\n\n48\n00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:35,287\nMarsha, these are letters to my family and friends back home … four letters!\n\n49\n00:03:35,489 --> 00:03:37,704\nIs there a post office near here?\n\n50\n00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,452\nUm, no.\n\n51\n00:03:40,571 --> 00:03:42,585\nThe post office is far from here.\n\n52\n00:03:42,685 --> 00:03:45,603\nBut there is a mailbox across from the store.\n\n53\n00:03:45,705 --> 00:03:47,116\nAwesome! Let’s go!\n\n54\n00:03:54,389 --> 00:03:56,808\nMarsha, now I need to buy stamps.\n\n55\n00:03:57,043 --> 00:03:58,150\nDo you have cash?\n\n56\n00:03:58,365 --> 00:04:01,096\nNo. Is there a bank near here?\n\n57\n00:04:01,213 --> 00:04:03,226\nThere is a bank behind you.\n\n58\n00:04:03,463 --> 00:04:05,074\nThanks, Marsha.\n\n59\n00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:07,505\nYou know our neighborhood so well.\n\n60\n00:04:13,173 --> 00:04:14,685\nNow I have cash.\n\n61\n00:04:14,889 --> 00:04:16,097\nI can buy stamps.\n\n62\n00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:18,917\nThat store sells stamps.\n\n63\n00:04:19,136 --> 00:04:20,241\nWait here.\n\n64\n00:04:20,579 --> 00:04:22,995\nI have stamps.\n\n65\n00:04:23,311 --> 00:04:24,920\nWow, you’re fast.\n\n66\n00:04:25,129 --> 00:04:34,694\nThank you, thank you letters, for sending my words… my love … to my family and friends -\n\n67\n00:04:38,938 --> 00:04:40,856\nDo you have more cash?\n\n68\n00:04:41,060 --> 00:04:42,269\nI do!\n\n69\n00:04:43,477 --> 00:04:45,291\nIce cream!!\n\n70\n00:04:47,919 --> 00:04:49,831\nI love my new neighborhood!\n\n71\n00:04:50,037 --> 00:04:52,152\nEverything is near our apartment!\n\n72\n00:04:52,353 --> 00:04:56,381\nEven hair salons*, and ice cream!\n\n73\n00:04:56,789 --> 00:04:58,105\nUntil next time!\n\n74\n00:04:59,048 --> 00:04:59,904\n*salon - n. a business that gives customers beauty treatments (such as haircuts)",
