		title		: "Lesson 12: Meet My Family",
		text		: "1\n00:00:16,881 --> 00:00:22,717\nHello! Washington, D.C. has many beautiful parks.\n\n2\n00:00:22,919 --> 00:00:31,372\nIn fact, this park reminds me of my home very far away.\n\n3\n00:00:34,595 --> 00:00:37,515\nAnna, here's your coffee.\n\n4\n00:00:37,615 --> 00:00:38,924\nThanks, Marsha.\n\n5\n00:00:39,024 --> 00:00:40,137\nWhat's wrong?\n\n6\n00:00:40,842 --> 00:00:43,561\nI'm thinking about my family.\n\n7\n00:00:43,969 --> 00:00:46,589\nI'm feeling homesick.\n\n8\n00:00:46,797 --> 00:00:49,018\nDo you want to talk about it?\n\n9\n00:00:49,119 --> 00:00:52,544\nSure! I have some photos.\n\n10\n00:00:54,254 --> 00:00:56,369\nYes. Yes, you do!\n\n11\n00:00:57,276 --> 00:00:58,787\nPhotos really help.\n\n12\n00:01:01,435 --> 00:01:05,462\nThis is my mother and this is my father.\n\n13\n00:01:05,775 --> 00:01:06,979\nThey are rodeo clowns.\n\n14\n00:01:07,580 --> 00:01:11,710\nWhat do rodeo clowns do?\n\n15\n00:01:12,426 --> 00:01:15,142\nThey make jokes at a rodeo.\n\n16\n00:01:15,030 --> 00:01:16,546\nThey make people laugh.\n\n17\n00:01:49,139 --> 00:01:51,553\nThat-That';s very different.\n\n18\n00:01:51,965 --> 00:01:54,279\nWho is that woman in the picture?\n\n19\n00:01:54,696 --> 00:01:57,115\nThat is my Aunt Lavender.\n\n20\n00:01:57,446 --> 00:01:59,559\nShe is my mom's sister.\n\n21\n00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:03,484\nShe loves gardening and makes spoons.\n\n22\n00:02:05,410 --> 00:02:07,421\nShe makes spoons?\n\n23\n00:02:07,531 --> 00:02:08,640\nOf course.\n\n24\n00:02:08,948 --> 00:02:12,469\nThat, too, is very different.\n\n25\n00:02:12,595 --> 00:02:14,615\nOh! This is my Uncle John.\n\n26\n00:02:14,917 --> 00:02:16,733\nHe is my father's brother.\n\n27\n00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:20,677\nWhat does Uncle John do?\n\n28\n00:02:20,777 --> 00:02:22,189\nHe's a chicken farmer.\n\n29\n00:02:22,296 --> 00:02:23,316\nAnd makes guitars.\n\n30\n00:02:23,421 --> 00:02:28,271\nHe's awesome, and I'm his favorite niece.\n\n31\n00:02:28,793 --> 00:02:29,800\nWho are they?\n\n32\n00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,611\nThey are my cousins.\n\n33\n00:02:31,916 --> 00:02:35,230\nThey are my Uncle John's daughter and son.\n\n34\n00:03:10,109 --> 00:03:11,218\nWhat do they do?\n\n35\n00:03:11,324 --> 00:03:14,140\nThey raise sheep and make sweaters.\n\n36\n00:03:14,464 --> 00:03:16,780\nYeah, that's not a surprise.\n\n37\n00:03:17,204 --> 00:03:21,334\nThanks for showing me your family photos.\n\n38\n00:03:21,453 --> 00:03:25,175\nYour family is very different.\n\n39\n00:03:25,292 --> 00:03:26,399\nI do feel better.\n\n40\n00:03:26,616 --> 00:03:28,238\nThanks for listening.\n\n41\n00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,754\nI have many more photos!\n\n42\n00:03:30,856 --> 00:03:35,903\nYeah. Yeah, you do.\n\n43\n00:03:36,847 --> 00:03:39,869\nWashington, DC is my new home.\n\n44\n00:03:40,173 --> 00:03:42,891\nBut I like remembering my old home, too.\n\n45\n00:03:49,731 --> 00:03:51,748\nThis is a family tree.\n\n46\n00:03:52,363 --> 00:03:55,777\nAnna tells Marsha about her parents.\n\n47\n00:03:56,179 --> 00:04:00,407\nHer mother and father are rodeo clowns.\n\n48\n00:04:01,020 --> 00:04:04,650\nHer father's parents are from Italy.\n\n49\n00:04:05,356 --> 00:04:08,679\nThese grandparents speak Italian.\n\n50\n00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:14,523\nAnna's mother's parents live in California.\n\n51\n00:04:15,147 --> 00:04:19,776\nThese grandparents have a farm and raise horses.\n\n52\n00:04:20,202 --> 00:04:25,138\nAnna's mother's sister is Aunt Lavender.\n\n53\n00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,150\nShe loves gardening.\n\n54\n00:04:27,568 --> 00:04:31,193\nAnna's father has a brother.\n\n55\n00:04:31,294 --> 00:04:33,403\nHis name is John.\n\n56\n00:04:33,719 --> 00:04:36,438\nUncle John makes guitars.\n\n57\n00:04:37,377 --> 00:04:40,700\nUncle John has a daughter and a son.\n\n58\n00:04:41,041 --> 00:04:43,307\nThey are Anna's cousins.\n\n59\n00:04:43,407 --> 00:04:45,673\nThey raise sheep.\n\n60\n00:04:47,505 --> 00:04:50,020\nAnna's brother has two children.\n\n61\n00:04:50,344 --> 00:04:53,665\nThey are Anna's niece and nephew.",
