		title		: "Lesson 14: How About This?",
		text		: "1\n00:00:16,717 --> 00:00:17,724\nHi, there!\n\n2\n00:00:17,926 --> 00:00:21,647\nIn Washington, D.C. people do many things in the evening.\n\n3\n00:00:21,747 --> 00:00:23,757\nThey go listen to music.\n\n4\n00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:26,080\nThey eat at a restaurant.\n\n5\n00:00:26,384 --> 00:00:27,994\nThey go to the theater.\n\n6\n00:00:28,195 --> 00:00:31,820\nTonight I am going to the theater with my friends.\n\n7\n00:00:32,321 --> 00:00:35,042\nBut I don’t know what clothes to wear.\n\n8\n00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:37,763\nMaybe this magazine can help.\n\n9\n00:00:39,779 --> 00:00:41,287\nHer clothes are beautiful!\n\n10\n00:00:41,590 --> 00:00:44,817\nI really want a friend like her to help me.\n\n11\n00:00:45,319 --> 00:00:48,538\nWho are you?\n\n12\n00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:50,759\nI am Genie!\n\n13\n00:00:51,262 --> 00:00:53,283\nYou want help.\n\n14\n00:00:53,489 --> 00:00:58,228\nI am here to help you find the right clothes!\n\n15\n00:00:58,435 --> 00:00:59,640\nAwesome!\n\n16\n00:00:59,862 --> 00:01:01,887\nHow about jeans and a t-shirt?\n\n17\n00:01:02,213 --> 00:01:07,148\nNo! Jeans and a t-shirt are too casual.\n\n18\n00:01:07,348 --> 00:01:09,965\nHow about something more formal?\n\n19\n00:01:10,381 --> 00:01:11,488\nSure!\n\n20\n00:01:15,089 --> 00:01:19,015\nWow! Genie, this dress is beautiful.\n\n21\n00:01:19,216 --> 00:01:23,945\nBut it’s not the right size. It’s too small.\n\n22\n00:01:24,350 --> 00:01:27,373\nYes, it is too small.\n\n23\n00:01:27,783 --> 00:01:30,803\nBut green looks great on you.\n\n24\n00:01:31,336 --> 00:01:32,242\nThanks.\n\n25\n00:01:32,572 --> 00:01:34,487\nTake off the green dress.\n\n26\n00:01:34,809 --> 00:01:39,942\nLet’s try a green shirt and a skirt.\n\n27\n00:02:12,813 --> 00:02:14,535\nOh, Genie!\n\n28\n00:02:14,837 --> 00:02:18,160\nThis green shirt is too large\n\n29\n00:02:18,461 --> 00:02:22,792\nand this orange skirt is too orange.\n\n30\n00:02:23,093 --> 00:02:27,622\nYes, the right size for you is medium.\n\n31\n00:02:28,143 --> 00:02:30,056\nLet’s try again.\n\n32\n00:02:33,315 --> 00:02:38,049\nOh, I don’t like this outfit.\n\n33\n00:02:38,377 --> 00:02:41,294\nNo. That does not match.\n\n34\n00:02:41,835 --> 00:02:43,041\nNothing.\n\n35\n00:02:46,229 --> 00:02:48,438\nThese clothes are formal\n\n36\n00:02:48,740 --> 00:02:52,266\na suit jacket, a dress shirt and a tie!\n\n37\n00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:53,575\nThey look great!\n\n38\n00:02:53,775 --> 00:02:57,800\nThose clothes look great … for a man!\n\n39\n00:02:58,129 --> 00:03:01,149\nSomething is wrong.\n\n40\n00:03:01,353 --> 00:03:02,661\nLet me see.\n\n41\n00:03:04,257 --> 00:03:06,483\nThere. Now try.\n\n42\n00:03:11,443 --> 00:03:12,866\nOh. Thanks!\n\n43\n00:03:13,272 --> 00:03:16,492\nNow these clothes look great on you!\n\n44\n00:03:16,593 --> 00:03:22,037\nThey do! Um, Genie, can you put on a gold belt?\n\n45\n00:03:22,351 --> 00:03:23,966\nSure!\n\n46\n00:03:25,995 --> 00:03:27,604\nThat looks great.\n\n47\n00:03:27,909 --> 00:03:30,426\nCan you put on a jacket?\n\n48\n00:03:31,148 --> 00:03:32,255\nWhy not?\n\n49\n00:03:33,481 --> 00:03:35,696\nI love the jacket!\n\n50\n00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:37,829\nHow about a hat?\n\n51\n00:03:38,272 --> 00:03:39,783\nWhy not?\n\n52\n00:04:14,934 --> 00:04:18,256\nMm, take off the hat.\n\n53\n00:04:21,051 --> 00:04:23,866\nThat’s better.\n\n54\n00:04:23,969 --> 00:04:26,799\nGenie, these clothes look and feel great!\n\n55\n00:04:27,017 --> 00:04:28,427\nLet’s go to the theater!\n\n56\n00:04:29,056 --> 00:04:32,585\nSorry, Anna. I have to help other friends.\n\n57\n00:04:32,996 --> 00:04:36,116\nGo to the magazine if you want me to help again.\n\n58\n00:04:36,544 --> 00:04:39,265\nThanks, Genie. Sure thing. Goodbye!\n\n59\n00:04:39,382 --> 00:04:40,288\nGoodbye!\n\n60\n00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:48,647\nThere are many places in DC to go for a great evening out!\n\n61\n00:04:48,850 --> 00:04:53,481\nAnd it’s nice to have a friend to help me look my best.\n\n62\n00:04:53,888 --> 00:04:55,702\nUntil next time! Bye!",
