		title		: "Lesson 21: Can You Come to the Party?",
		text		: "1\n00:00:17,950 --> 00:00:18,960\nHi there!\n\n2\n00:00:19,161 --> 00:00:22,182\nWashington, D.C. has some great coffee shops.\n\n3\n00:00:22,686 --> 00:00:26,010\nMy favorite is this one -- Busboys & Poets.\n\n4\n00:00:26,612 --> 00:00:29,332\nActually it’s more than a coffee shop.\n\n5\n00:00:29,736 --> 00:00:33,263\nIt’s also a bookstore, a restaurant and a theater!\n\n6\n00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:36,091\nMarsha and I love coming here.\n\n7\n00:00:36,391 --> 00:00:40,519\nHey, Anna, my friend is having a party on Saturday.\n\n8\n00:00:40,821 --> 00:00:42,028\nCan you come with me?\n\n9\n00:00:42,129 --> 00:00:44,248\nSorry, I can’t come with you.\n\n10\n00:00:44,551 --> 00:00:46,564\nI have to get my driver’s license.\n\n11\n00:00:46,866 --> 00:00:49,085\nWill you be busy all day?\n\n12\n00:00:49,587 --> 00:00:50,493\nI don’t know.\n\n13\n00:00:50,807 --> 00:00:53,424\nFirst, I have to take a test on the computer.\n\n14\n00:00:53,731 --> 00:00:56,451\nThen I have to take a test in the car.\n\n15\n00:01:54,675 --> 00:01:58,902\nBut you have to take the test during the day, don't you?\n\n16\n00:01:59,003 --> 00:01:59,813\nYes.\n\n17\n00:02:00,114 --> 00:02:01,521\nThe party is at night.\n\n18\n00:02:01,839 --> 00:02:07,073\nOh. Then I can come with you to the party on Saturday night.\n\n19\n00:02:07,574 --> 00:02:08,480\nGreat!\n\n20\n00:02:08,882 --> 00:02:10,606\nI have to help my friend with the party.\n\n21\n00:02:10,912 --> 00:02:12,019\nCan you help me?\n\n22\n00:02:12,462 --> 00:02:13,772\nSure. That sounds like fun.\n\n23\n00:02:14,393 --> 00:02:17,410\nEveryone has to bring something or do something.\n\n24\n00:02:17,711 --> 00:02:21,436\nYou can bring food, or you can perform.\n\n25\n00:02:21,738 --> 00:02:23,551\nReally, I can perform?\n\n26\n00:02:23,853 --> 00:02:27,175\nYou can! Can you?\n\n27\n00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:31,605\nYes! I can recite poetry.\n\n28\n00:02:33,075 --> 00:02:34,422\n- A poem -\n\n29\n00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:37,241\nLight dark\n\n30\n00:02:38,045 --> 00:02:39,050\nLight dark\n\n31\n00:02:39,351 --> 00:02:41,464\nDarkness\n\n32\n00:02:41,968 --> 00:02:42,875\nDark\n\n33\n00:02:42,988 --> 00:02:46,708\nIn this country, nobody recites poetry at parties.\n\n34\n00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:51,072\nUm … can you do anything else?\n\n35\n00:02:51,573 --> 00:02:56,406\nHmm, yes. I can do a card trick.\n\n36\n00:02:57,676 --> 00:03:02,813\nYour card is the 10 of diamonds!\n\n37\n00:03:02,786 --> 00:03:04,097\nNo?\n\n38\n00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:06,596\nPick a card. Any card.\n\n39\n00:03:07,704 --> 00:03:09,741\nHere, just pick this one.\n\n40\n00:03:09,842 --> 00:03:11,050\nGreat!\n\n41\n00:03:12,345 --> 00:03:15,467\nAnna, maybe you can just bring food.\n\n42\n00:03:15,667 --> 00:03:17,678\nNo, I can’t cook.\n\n43\n00:03:17,980 --> 00:03:20,494\nAnd I really want to perform.\n\n44\n00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:26,642\nYou know, there is one thing I can do.\n\n45\n00:03:27,425 --> 00:03:29,950\nTrouble in mind.\n\n46\n00:03:30,152 --> 00:03:31,863\nI’m blue...\n\n47\n00:03:32,265 --> 00:03:35,894\nBut I won't be blue always\n\n48\n00:03:37,105 --> 00:03:42,842\nThe sun's gonna shine in my back door some day.*\n\n49\n00:04:35,721 --> 00:04:37,131\nThat’s it!\n\n50\n00:04:37,432 --> 00:04:39,041\nYou can sing at the party.\n\n51\n00:04:39,645 --> 00:04:41,556\nNow, I have to go shopping for food.\n\n52\n00:04:41,959 --> 00:04:42,766\nCan I help?\n\n53\n00:04:42,866 --> 00:04:44,075\nI’m not busy right now.\n\n54\n00:04:44,276 --> 00:04:46,088\nSure, let’s go!\n\n55\n00:04:46,591 --> 00:04:47,500\nWe have to go.\n\n56\n00:04:47,617 --> 00:04:49,024\nI have to help Marsha shop.\n\n57\n00:04:49,231 --> 00:04:51,663\nAnd I have to practice my song!\n\n58\n00:04:52,179 --> 00:04:53,388\nTrouble in mind.\n\n59\n00:04:53,706 --> 00:04:54,914\nI’m blue...\n\n60\n00:04:55,225 --> 00:04:56,231\nUntil next time!\n\n61\n00:04:56,551 --> 00:05:00,138\n*The song Trouble in Mind was written by jazz pianist Richard M. Jones.",
