		title		: "Lesson 37: Let's Agree to Disagree",
		text		: "1\n00:00:09,702 --> 00:00:15,931\nYou know, I am from the country and sometimes I miss it.\n\n2\n00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:21,314\nBut I really like life in the city!\n\n3\n00:00:25,782 --> 00:00:27,805\nI love the city.\n\n4\n00:00:27,805 --> 00:00:32,022\nOh, look. Someone lost a bag.\n\n5\n00:00:33,154 --> 00:00:35,554\nMaybe it's theirs. \n\n6\n00:00:40,548 --> 00:00:42,342\nExcuse me.\n\n7\n00:00:42,340 --> 00:00:44,194\nIs this bag yours?\n\n8\n00:00:44,194 --> 00:00:45,805\nNo. It's not mine.\n\n9\n00:00:45,805 --> 00:00:47,451\nIt might be hers.\n\n10\n00:00:47,450 --> 00:00:48,777\nThank you.\n\n11\n00:00:54,285 --> 00:00:57,645\nExcuse me. Is this bag yours?\n\n12\n00:00:57,645 --> 00:01:00,320\nNo. It's not mine.\n\n13\n00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,657\nIt might be his.\n\n14\n00:01:01,657 --> 00:01:02,994\nThank you.\n\n15\n00:01:08,468 --> 00:01:11,588\nHello. Is this bag yours?\n\n16\n00:01:11,580 --> 00:01:14,422\nYes, that's mine.\n\n17\n00:01:14,422 --> 00:01:17,725\nThese are all my travel things.\n\n18\n00:01:17,725 --> 00:01:21,280\nThank you, thank you!\n\n19\n00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:23,542\nAre you okay?\n\n20\n00:01:23,542 --> 00:01:26,720\nYou seem ... nervous.\n\n21\n00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:30,720\nWell, this is my first visit to Washington, D.C.\n\n22\n00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:33,720\nI'm from a small town in the country.\n\n23\n00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:36,102\nI feel a little lost.\n\n24\n00:01:45,382 --> 00:01:47,862\nI am from the country too!\n\n25\n00:01:47,862 --> 00:01:50,057\nAnd I understand.\n\n26\n00:01:50,057 --> 00:01:53,988\nWhen I first came here, I felt lost ... \n\n27\n00:01:53,980 --> 00:01:56,011\nall the time.\n\n28\n00:01:56,034 --> 00:02:00,822\nSo, do you like living in the country or in the city?\n\n29\n00:02:01,474 --> 00:02:05,165\nI like to live in the city.\n\n30\n00:02:05,165 --> 00:02:06,640\nWhy?\n\n31\n00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:09,291\nThe city is exciting!\n\n32\n00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:12,445\nIt has more culture than the country.\n\n33\n00:02:12,445 --> 00:02:15,862\nThere are many museums and restaurants.\n\n34\n00:02:15,862 --> 00:02:19,440\nEvery night, there is theater and music.\n\n35\n00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:22,685\nAnd, there are more jobs.\n\n36\n00:02:22,685 --> 00:02:25,685\nThat is why I'm here.\n\n37\n00:02:25,685 --> 00:02:28,685\nWell, I agree.\n\n38\n00:02:28,685 --> 00:02:31,645\nThere is more culture in the city \n\n39\n00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:34,297\nand there might be more jobs.\n\n40\n00:02:34,297 --> 00:02:36,902\nBut the country has more nature!\n\n41\n00:02:36,902 --> 00:02:40,262\nIt's peaceful and beautiful.\n\n42\n00:02:40,262 --> 00:02:43,988\nThere are more trees and mountains.\n\n43\n00:02:43,988 --> 00:02:46,000\nThe air is clean. \n\n44\n00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000\nYou can go hiking and camping.\n\n45\n00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000\nThe city is not beautiful.\n\n46\n00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,497\nIt's noisy and dirty.\n\n47\n00:02:55,497 --> 00:02:57,142\nI disagree.\n\n48\n00:02:57,142 --> 00:03:01,360\nI think all the different buildings are beautiful.\n\n49\n00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:05,417\nAnd I like to watch all the different people.\n\n50\n00:03:14,685 --> 00:03:17,245\nThat's another thing that is different.\n\n51\n00:03:17,245 --> 00:03:20,948\nPeople in the country are friendly.\n\n52\n00:03:20,948 --> 00:03:23,360\nThey always say \"hello!\"\n\n53\n00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,434\nHere, no one says \"hello.\"\n\n54\n00:03:26,434 --> 00:03:30,342\nI think city people are rude.\n\n55\n00:03:30,342 --> 00:03:34,788\nWell, I agree. Country people are friendly.\n\n56\n00:03:34,788 --> 00:03:38,617\nBut I don't think city people are rude.\n\n57\n00:03:38,617 --> 00:03:40,662\nI think they're just busy.\n\n58\n00:03:40,662 --> 00:03:42,674\nThat's a good point.\n\n59\n00:03:42,674 --> 00:03:43,840\nLook at me.\n\n60\n00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:47,142\nI live in the city and I said \"hello\" to you.\n\n61\n00:03:47,142 --> 00:03:49,931\nBut you are from the country.\n\n62\n00:03:49,931 --> 00:03:51,771\nI have an idea.\n\n63\n00:03:51,771 --> 00:03:57,680\nLet's say \"hello!\" to people -- to many people!\n\n64\n00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:59,588\nWhat? Why?\n\n65\n00:03:59,588 --> 00:04:05,542\nWell, if we say \"hello,\" maybe they will say \"hello\" to other people ... Hello!\n\n66\n00:04:05,542 --> 00:04:08,994\n... and they will say \"hello\" to more people!\n\n67\n00:04:08,994 --> 00:04:11,657\nThat's a great idea! \n\n68\n00:04:11,650 --> 00:04:13,805\nI'm glad you found my bag.\n\n69\n00:04:13,805 --> 00:04:17,520\nCome on. Let's go say \"hello\" to people.\n\n70\n00:04:38,285 --> 00:04:41,234\nWe don't have to agree with people.\n\n71\n00:04:41,234 --> 00:04:43,131\nThey have their opinions.\n\n72\n00:04:43,131 --> 00:04:44,960\nWe have ours.\n\n73\n00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:50,285\nAnd as we like to say, you can always agree to disagree!\n\n74\n00:04:50,285 --> 00:04:51,942\nUntil next time...!\n\n75\n00:04:51,942 --> 00:04:53,634\nHello!",
