		title		: "Lesson 47: How Can I help?",
		text		: "1\n00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,668\nHi, Pete. What are you doing?\n\n2\n00:00:11,668 --> 00:00:13,794\nOh! Hi, Anna.\n\n3\n00:00:13,794 --> 00:00:18,171\nRight now, I am fixing my car.\n\n4\n00:00:18,171 --> 00:00:20,228\nHow’s it going?\n\n5\n00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:23,817\nIt’s going … not so good.\n\n6\n00:00:23,817 --> 00:00:27,462\nHow can I help? I was planning to visit some friends.\n\n7\n00:00:27,462 --> 00:00:29,542\nBut if you need help, I can help.\n\n8\n00:00:29,542 --> 00:00:30,582\nI like helping.\n\n9\n00:00:30,582 --> 00:00:34,880\nAnna, I can fix it myself. But thanks.\n\n10\n00:00:39,828 --> 00:00:43,462\nPete, I think I found your problem.\n\n11\n00:00:43,462 --> 00:00:45,794\nThese are spark plugs.\n\n12\n00:00:45,794 --> 00:00:47,702\nThey start the engine.\n\n13\n00:00:47,702 --> 00:00:49,782\nI know that, Anna.\n\n14\n00:00:49,782 --> 00:00:55,108\nBut there were too many spark plugs … in there.\n\n15\n00:00:55,108 --> 00:00:57,314\nSo I took out the extra ones.\n\n16\n00:00:57,314 --> 00:00:59,588\nThere are no extras, Pete.\n\n17\n00:00:59,588 --> 00:01:02,588\nYou need all of them.\n\n18\n00:01:20,457 --> 00:01:24,068\nPete, can you fix a car yourself?\n\n19\n00:01:24,068 --> 00:01:29,817\nWell, Anna, last night I was watching the online video course,\n\n20\n00:01:29,817 --> 00:01:32,205\n“You CAN Fix a Car Yourself!”\n\n21\n00:01:32,205 --> 00:01:36,880\nYes, you CAN fix your car yourself!\n\n22\n00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:39,680\nAnd I watched the first 10 lessons.\n\n23\n00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:42,274\nSo, I think I know what I’m doing.\n\n24\n00:01:42,274 --> 00:01:44,548\nHow many lessons are there?\n\n25\n00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,520\nFour hundred and fifty.\n\n26\n00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:51,165\n450! That'll take too long! \n\n27\n00:01:51,257 --> 00:01:55,900\nIf I fix your car, I'll have it running in 10 to 15 minutes.\n\n28\n00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:58,148\nWhere’re your tools?\n\n29\n00:01:58,148 --> 00:02:01,148\nI have this.\n\n30\n00:02:02,891 --> 00:02:05,005\nAnd this.\n\n31\n00:02:05,005 --> 00:02:09,108\nGreat. Um, I’ll get my tools.\n\n32\n00:02:09,108 --> 00:02:10,765\nI’ll be back in a flash!\n\n33\n00:02:10,765 --> 00:02:13,234\nBut, Anna, I don’t need your ...\n\n34\n00:02:13,234 --> 00:02:14,297\n… help.\n\n35\n00:02:14,297 --> 00:02:20,240\nPete, when I was a teenager, I was fixing cars -- myself.\n\n36\n00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:24,160\nI learned from a master.\n\n37\n00:02:29,977 --> 00:02:31,805\nYou can trust me.\n\n38\n00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,662\nOkay.\n\n39\n00:02:52,342 --> 00:02:56,308\nGreat! But we need teamwork.\n\n40\n00:02:56,308 --> 00:02:58,000\nYou sit in the car.\n\n41\n00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,360\nWhen I say “go,” you start the engine.\n\n42\n00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:04,845\nOkay, go! ​\n\n43\n00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,514\nStop!\n\n44\n00:03:10,731 --> 00:03:12,400\nOkay, go! Huh.\n\n45\n00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,828\nIt's not starting!\n\n46\n00:03:17,897 --> 00:03:19,520\nIt’s not starting!\n\n47\n00:03:19,570 --> 00:03:21,005\nWhat’s wrong?\n\n48\n00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:25,588\nThis car is stupid … stupid, stupid!\n\n49\n00:03:25,588 --> 00:03:28,262\nPete, kicking the tires will not help.\n\n50\n00:03:28,262 --> 00:03:31,074\nWell, you did not help, Anna.\n\n51\n00:03:31,074 --> 00:03:32,662\nYou did not help!!\n\n52\n00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:35,660\nPete, Pete! Pull yourself together, man.\n\n53\n00:03:35,660 --> 00:03:38,660\nGive me the keys.\n\n54\n00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:44,240\nI must feel the key in the ignition and turn it myself.\n\n55\n00:03:56,182 --> 00:03:58,102\nUse the key, Anna.\n\n56\n00:03:59,097 --> 00:04:01,942\nTurn the key, Anna.\n\n57\n00:04:03,714 --> 00:04:08,788\nWhat are you forgetting, Anna?\n\n58\n00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:13,108\nPete. Pete.\n\n59\n00:04:13,108 --> 00:04:14,617\nWhat?\n\n60\n00:04:14,617 --> 00:04:16,108\nYou are out of gas.\nWhat?\n\n61\n00:04:16,108 --> 00:04:19,108\nYou are out of gas.\n\n62\n00:04:19,108 --> 00:04:22,605\nI can’t be out of gas.\n\n63\n00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:29,634\nI’m out of gas. Sorry, Anna.\n\n64\n00:04:32,685 --> 00:04:35,040\nI’ll go get some.\n\n65\n00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:38,040\nPete. You relax.\n\n66\n00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,102\nClean your face.\n\n67\n00:04:40,102 --> 00:04:44,708\nYou can watch the rest of your online video course.\n\n68\n00:04:44,708 --> 00:04:47,988\nIt’ll be faster if I go … in a flash.\n\n69\n00:04:47,988 --> 00:04:49,977\nUntil next time …",
