		title		: "Lesson 48: Have You Ever ...?",
		text		: "1\n00:00:09,497 --> 00:00:10,548\nHello!\n\n2\n00:00:10,674 --> 00:00:16,182\nI have lived in Washington, D.C. for a long time now.\n\n3\n00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:18,742\nAnd I have done a lot.\n\n4\n00:00:20,102 --> 00:00:23,954\nI feel that I know this city pretty well.\n\n5\n00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:29,268\nThat's the wrong way.\n\n6\n00:00:29,268 --> 00:00:30,662\nWhere is it again?\n\n7\n00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:42,525\nExcuse me, can I help you?\n\n8\n00:00:42,525 --> 00:00:45,840\nHave we met before?\n\n9\n00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:47,794\nI don’t think so.\n\n10\n00:00:47,794 --> 00:00:50,057\nI’ve just flown in from Boston.\n\n11\n00:00:50,057 --> 00:00:50,960\nMy name is Jean.\n\n12\n00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:54,160\nHi, Jean! I'm Anna.\n\n13\n00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:57,942\nI really feel like we’ve met before.\n\n14\n00:00:57,942 --> 00:01:01,245\nAnyway, how can I help?\n\n15\n00:01:01,245 --> 00:01:06,480\nI want to see an interesting museum but I don’t know which one.\n\n16\n00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,320\nI can help with that.\n\n17\n00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:11,611\nI’ve lived in Washington, D.C. a long time.\n\n18\n00:01:11,611 --> 00:01:15,280\nI think I’ve seen all the museums.\n\n19\n00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:19,691\nWow, thanks. So, tell me, which museums are good?\n\n20\n00:01:19,691 --> 00:01:22,691\nWell, they are all good.\n\n21\n00:01:22,691 --> 00:01:24,742\nBut they’re all different.\n\n22\n00:01:24,742 --> 00:01:32,548\nThere are science museums and history museums and art and culture museums.\n\n23\n00:01:32,994 --> 00:01:36,914\nI want to see an unusual museum.\n\n24\n00:01:36,914 --> 00:01:39,914\nI like the Sculpture Garden.\n\n25\n00:01:39,914 --> 00:01:44,617\nHave you ever seen sculptures in a garden?\n\n26\n00:01:44,610 --> 00:01:49,645\nIt is really artistic!\n\n27\n00:01:49,645 --> 00:01:53,120\nI have never seen a garden of sculptures!\n\n28\n00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,754\nI’ll write that on my list!\n\n29\n00:02:05,885 --> 00:02:10,742\nHave you been to the Museum of the American Indian?\n\n30\n00:02:10,742 --> 00:02:13,742\nI’ve visited that museum many times.\n\n31\n00:02:13,742 --> 00:02:16,742\nIt is very peaceful.\n\n32\n00:02:16,742 --> 00:02:20,880\nI have always liked American Indian culture.\n\n33\n00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,742\nI’ll put that on my list.\n\n34\n00:02:22,742 --> 00:02:25,742\nDo you have any other suggestions?\n\n35\n00:02:25,742 --> 00:02:32,091\nWell, if you like plants, you can visit the U.S. Botanic Gardens.\n\n36\n00:02:32,091 --> 00:02:36,148\nIt's very organic.\n\n37\n00:02:36,148 --> 00:02:39,017\nI have always loved plants.\n\n38\n00:02:39,017 --> 00:02:41,371\nI’ll write that on my list, too!\n\n39\n00:02:41,371 --> 00:02:46,194\nWow, you know so much about D.C.’s museums.\n\n40\n00:02:47,222 --> 00:02:51,531\nWell, I have lived here for over a year.\n\n41\n00:02:51,531 --> 00:02:59,622\nYou’re so lucky to live in such a beautiful city filled with so many museums and a zoo!\n\n42\n00:02:59,622 --> 00:03:02,742\nWhat? D.C. has a zoo?\n\n43\n00:03:02,742 --> 00:03:05,520\nYes, and it’s beautiful.\n\n44\n00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:11,851\nYou’ve lived here for so long and you haven’t been to the zoo?\n\n45\n00:03:11,851 --> 00:03:14,651\nI've never been to D.C.’s zoo.\n\n46\n00:03:14,650 --> 00:03:17,462\nI've never been to any zoos!\n\n47\n00:03:25,245 --> 00:03:28,674\nYou have never seen zoo animals?\n\n48\n00:03:28,674 --> 00:03:31,348\nI grew up on a farm, Jean.\n\n49\n00:03:31,348 --> 00:03:34,348\nI've known farm animals my whole life.\n\n50\n00:03:34,348 --> 00:03:43,085\nBut the zoo has lions and elephants and zebras!\n\n51\n00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:49,542\nIf you have never seen a real, live elephant, you must.\n\n52\n00:03:49,542 --> 00:03:52,542\nThey are so majestic.\n\n53\n00:03:53,451 --> 00:03:58,697\nI will. I will!  There.\n\n54\n00:03:58,697 --> 00:04:02,811\nI’ve written my own must-see zoo animal list!\n\n55\n00:04:02,811 --> 00:04:05,811\nHave fun at the zoo and thanks, Anna!\n\n56\n00:04:05,811 --> 00:04:09,051\nHave fun at the museums, Jean! And thank YOU!\n\n57\n00:04:38,502 --> 00:04:41,245\nThis has been awesome!\n\n58\n00:04:41,245 --> 00:04:45,554\nAnd I have seen every animal on my list!\n\n59\n00:04:45,554 --> 00:04:50,502\nJean, the tourist, helped me see more of my city.\n\n60\n00:04:50,502 --> 00:04:54,857\nBut where have I seen her before?\n\n61\n00:04:54,857 --> 00:04:56,045\nOh well.\n\n62\n00:04:56,045 --> 00:04:57,714\nUntil next time …",
